8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 364, L.D. 832, “An Act to Provide Funds
10 to Reduce the Debt of the Vassalboro Sanitary District”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Direct the Department of Environmental Protection to Provide Funding to
13 Public Wastewater Systems for the Repayment of Loans'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 38 MRSA §411-C, sub-§2, ¶B, as enacted by PL 2009, c. 377, §3, is
17 amended to read:
18 B. To forgive or provide funding for the repayment of loans held by public wastewater
19 systems for the acquisition, planning, design, construction, reconstruction,
20 enlargement, repair, protection or improvement of public wastewater systems and
21 treatment facilities and water pollution abatement systems;
22 Sec. 2. Maine Clean Water Fund; loan repayment competitive process. The
23 Department of Environmental Protection shall use the funds transferred in accordance with
24 section 3 and deposited into the Maine Clean Water Fund established in the Maine Revised
25 Statutes, Title 38, section 411-C to provide funding for the repayment of loans held by
26 public wastewater systems in accordance with Title 38, section 411-C, subsection 2,
27 paragraph B. The department shall establish a competitive process by which public
28 wastewater systems, including sanitary districts established in accordance with Title 38,
29 chapter 11 and sewer districts as defined in Title 38, section 1032, subsection 3, may apply
30 to the department for funds for loan repayment. In evaluating applications for loan
31 repayment and awarding funds under the competitive process, the department shall seek to
32 provide funding to public wastewater systems most at risk of defaulting on their debt by
33 considering the amount of debt held by the public wastewater system, the necessary rate
34 increases to repay that debt, the number of customers of the public wastewater system and
35 any other factors as determined by the department. The department shall make the first
36 award of funds in accordance with this section by July 1, 2026.
