17 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
18 number to read consecutively.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. It authorizes the Maine Clean
2211 Water Fund to be used for repayment of loans held by public wastewater systems. It
2222 requires the Department of Environmental Protection to establish a competitive process to
2233 use $3,000,000 in funds from the Maine Clean Water Fund to provide funding for the
2244 repayment of loans held by public wastewater systems. It requires the department, in
2255 evaluating applications for loan repayment and awarding funds under the competitive
2266 process, to seek to provide funding to public wastewater systems most at risk of defaulting
2277 on their debt. The department is required to make an initial award of funds by July 1, 2026.
